EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to artificial intelligence; defining “artificial
intelligence” in the context of emergency management;
requiring emergency management plans prepared by the
Governor and each plan adopted by a state or local
governmental agency to include provisions ensuring that
final decisions regarding emergency response planning
and the allocation of resources in response to an
emergency are not made by artificial intelligence;
prohibiting a public utility from using artificial
intelligence to make a final decision regarding whether to
reduce or shutdown utility service in response to a
disaster or emergency; and providing other matters
properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law provides for the development of emergency management plans by
2 state and local governmental agencies. (NRS 414.040) Existing law also authorizes
3 the development of a state emergency management plan. (NRS 414.060) Section 3
4 of this bill requires such emergency management plans to include certain provisions
5 to ensure final decisions regarding emergency response planning and the allocation
6 of resources in response to an emergency are not made by artificial intelligence.
7 Section 2 of this bill defines “artificial intelligence” in the context of
8 emergency management.
