THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 414 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto the provisions set forth as sections 2 and 3 of this act.
3 Sec. 2. “Artificial intelligence” means a machine-based
4 system that can, for a given set of human-defined objectives, make
5 predictions, recommendations or decisions influencing real or
6 virtual environments.
7 Sec. 3. Any state emergency management plan prepared
8 pursuant to NRS 414.060 and each plan for emergency operations
9 described in subparagraph (2) of paragraph (b) of subsection 4 of
10 NRS 414.040 that is adopted by a state or local governmental
11 agency must include provisions ensuring that final decisions
12 regarding emergency response planning and the allocation of
13 resources in response to an emergency are not made by artificial
14 intelligence but rather by a natural person.
15 Sec. 4. NRS 414.030 is hereby amended to read as follows:
16 414.030 As used in this chapter, the words and terms defined
17 in NRS 414.031 to 414.038, inclusive, and section 2 of this act have
18 the meanings ascribed to them in those sections.
19 Sec. 5. Chapter 704 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
20 thereto a new section to read as follows:
21 1. A public utility shall not use artificial intelligence to make
22 a final decision regarding whether to reduce or shutdown utility
23 service in response to a disaster or emergency.
24 2. As used in this section:
25 (a) “Artificial intelligence” has the meaning ascribed to it in
26 section 2 of this act.
27 (b) “Disaster” has the meaning ascribed to it in NRS 414.0035.
28 (c) “Emergency” has the meaning ascribed to it in
29 NRS 414.0345.
